# Error -102 on Opening Courses V1 ‚Äì Instant Fix

**Symptom:** Browser shows Error Code -102 when opening `http://127.0.0.1:5173/#/courses/opening-courses-v1` (tab may reload or go blank). This is a **renderer/tab crash**, not ‚Äúconnection refused.‚Äù

**Apply these fixes in `my-app/src/views/Courses.vue` in order:**

## 0. Defer layout (if -102 persists)

- Add `openingV1Ready = ref(false)` and a `watch(isOpeningCoursesV1, ...)` that sets `openingV1Ready = true` only after a short delay (e.g. `setTimeout(..., 50)`) when the route is opening-courses-v1; clear the timer in `onUnmounted`.
- In the template, wrap the opening-v1-layout in `v-if="openingV1Ready"` and add `<div v-else class="opening-v1-placeholder">` so the full layout does not render on first paint. Add minimal `.opening-v1-placeholder` CSS (flex, min-height, background).

## 1. Dedicated scroll ref (main cause)

The scroll container for Opening Courses V1 must **not** share `coursesContentRef` with the other panel (v-else branch). Sharing causes the scroll listener to attach to the wrong or torn-down node and can crash the tab.

- **Add:** `const openingScrollRef = ref(null)`
- **Template:** On the opening-v1 scroll container (the div with class `opening-v1-scroll`), use `ref="openingScrollRef"` (not `ref="coursesContentRef"`).
- **Scroll watcher:** Depend on `openingScrollRef`, not `coursesContentRef`:
  - `watch(() => [isOpeningCoursesV1.value, openingScrollRef.value], ...)`
  - Inside the handler and in `onOpeningContentScroll`, use `openingScrollRef.value` only.

## 2. Safe FEN / position helpers

- **parseFEN(fen):** Must never throw. Validate `fen` (null/undefined/string), validate `position` and `rows.length === 8`. On invalid input or in catch, return a safe fallback (e.g. parse STARTING_FEN in a try/catch or return `[]`).
- **getPositionAtEndOfLine(moves):** Wrap body in try/catch; on error return `{ fen: STARTING_FEN, lastMove: null }`.

## 3. Scroll listener

- **onOpeningContentScroll:** Wrap body in try/catch. Guard `scrollTop` (e.g. `typeof el.scrollTop === 'number' ? el.scrollTop : 0`).
- **Watch cleanup:** Wrap `addEventListener` / `removeEventListener` and `lastOpeningScrollTop.value = el.scrollTop` in try/catch.

## 4. Opening card watcher

- **setTimeout callback** that calls `playOpeningThirdMove`: wrap in try/catch; on error set `openingCardAnimatingMove.value = null`.
- Keep **clearOpeningAutoMove()** in **onUnmounted**.

## 5. Verify

- Build: `cd my-app && npm run build`
- Open `http://127.0.0.1:5173/#/courses/opening-courses-v1` (with dev server running). No -102.

**Reference in code:** In Courses.vue near the opening card watch, keep a one-line comment:  
`// If Error -102 on /#/courses/opening-courses-v1: apply .cursor/rules/opening-courses-v1-crash-102.mdc`
